The choir from South Africa has garnered international attention for their performances! They put their spin on "Higher Love" by Whitney Houston and Kygo's Steve Winwood. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's Ndlovu Youth Choir have once again wowed the world on America's Got Talent. The Limpopo choir received a rousing standing ovation after a stunning performance in the semi-finals. READ: Ndlovu Youth Choir give electric quarter-final performance on AGT They put a stunning African spin on "Higher Love". "We pray that our performance was a reminder to the world that we are all connected by our spirit of humanity. Love is an unbreakable force which will always conquer hate," said the group on their official social media accounts. The results of the show will be announced on Wednesday.